===實驗用===
[[File:Rabbits_at_Polyface_Farm.jpg|thumb]]

兔子在過去和現在都被用於實驗室當中，兔子常被用於生產[[疫苗|疫苗]][[抗體|抗體]]，以及在[[毒物學|毒物學]]上研究各種物質對人類[[男性生殖系統|男性生殖系統]]的影響。在1972年，在[[美國|美國]]有450,000隻兔子被用於實驗，到了2006年，這數字減為240,000隻。<ref>{{cite journal |title=A review of trends in animal use in the United States (1972–2006) |last1=Kulpa-Eddy |first1=Jodie |last2=Snyder |first2=Margaret |last3=Stokes |first3=William |journal=AATEX |issue=14, Special Issue: Proceedings of the 6th World Congress on Alternatives & Animal Use in the Life Sciences, August 21–25, 2007 |date=2008 |publisher=Japanese Society for Alternatives to Animal Experiments |pages=163–165 |url=http://www.soc.nii.ac.jp/jsaae/zasshi/WC6_PC/paper163.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313093813/http://www.soc.nii.ac.jp/jsaae/zasshi/WC6_PC/paper163.pdf |archive-date=2012-03-13 |access-date=October 3, 2015 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>紐西蘭兔是最常被養來用於研究和測試的兔子品種。根據美國國家衛生院出版的《環境衛生前景》的說法，兔子「在研究[[化学物质|化学物质]]和其他[[刺激_(生理学)|刺激物]]對男性生殖系統的影響方面，是一種極度重要的模型生物。」<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Morton |first=Daniel |title=The use of rabbits in male reproductive toxicology |date=April 1988 |journal=[[Environmental_Health_Perspectives|Environmental Health Perspectives]] |volume=77 |pages=5–9 |publisher=U.S. National Institutes of Health |doi=10.2307/3430622 |pmc=1474531 |pmid=3383822 |jstor=3430622}}</ref>另外根據美國保護動物協會（Humane Society）的說法，兔子也大量被用於支氣管[[氣喘|氣喘]]、[[中風|中風]][[預防|預防]][[療法|療法]]、[[囊腫性纖維化|囊腫性纖維化]]、[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]和[[癌症|癌症]]等的研究當中。

將兔子用於[[德萊茲測試|德萊茲測試]]這種化妝品動物測試當中的作法，<ref>{{cite journal |title=The Draize Eye Test and ''in vitro'' alternatives:A left-handed marriage? |first=M. K. |last=Prinsen |journal=Toxicology in Vitro |date=2006 |volume=20 |issue=1 |pages=78–81 |doi=10.1016/j.tiv.2005.06.030 |pmid=16055303}}</ref><ref name="ScienceDirect 2018 pp. 673–747">{{cite web | title=Special Senses | website=ScienceDirect | date=2018-01-01 | doi=10.1016/B978-0-12-809841-7.00022-8 | url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B9780128098417000228#s0100 | access-date=2020-06-11 | pages=673–747 | archive-date=2020-06-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611074326/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B9780128098417000228#s0100 | dead-url=no }}</ref>已被一些動物權團體給視為[[動物試驗|動物試驗]]當中對動物的殘忍行為的一個例子。<ref name="PETA 2010">{{cite web | title=Rabbits in Laboratories | website=PETA | date=2010-06-23 | url=https://www.peta.org/issues/animals-used-for-experimentation/rabbits-laboratories/ | access-date=2020-06-11 | archive-date=2020-06-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609035454/https://www.peta.org/issues/animals-used-for-experimentation/rabbits-laboratories/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Scientific American 2009">{{cite web | title=Do Cosmetic Companies Still Test on Live Animals? | website=Scientific American | date=2009-08-06 | url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/cosmetics-animal-testing/ | access-date=2020-06-11 | archive-date=2020-06-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611074327/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/cosmetics-animal-testing/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>白兔常被用於[[德萊茲測試|德萊茲測試]]當中，是因為白兔的眼淚較其他動物來得少，且眼睛缺乏色素使得藥品潛在的影響較容易觀察所致。<ref>{{cite book |last=Dawn |first=Karen |authorlink=Karen Dawn |title=Thanking the Monkey: Rethinking the Way we Treat Animals |date=2008 |publisher=[[HarperCollins|HarperCollins]] |location=New York |isbn=978-0-06-135185-3 |pages=239–40 |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=pt7ZirPwG1sC&dq=thanking+the+monkey |access-date=March 12, 2013}}</ref>

